  "body": "### Description\n\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\n*Type*: Bug\n*Summary*: \nOn some Android devices (Galaxy S6, Android 6.0.1) beta warning popup and Welcome screen are overlapping each other if app was moved to background and back after account is created. \n\nNote: on another real Android device Pixel XL, Android 9 it can't be reproduced\n![Screenshot_20190412-183639](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/56052685-5e29a600-5d52-11e9-84a1-1d0e263c4805.png)\n\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\n\n\n#### Expected behavior\n1. popup is shown on top\n2. behind popup Welcome screen is shown\n\n#### Actual behavior\nPicture from the Welcome screen is shown above beta warning popup\n\n\n### Reproduction\n\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\nvideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=1_ttV2n6PmcfDIERjD0E1zQaufb03V-O9\n- Open Status\n- Create new account\n- when beta warning is shown move app to background\n- move app to foreground \n\n\n\n### Additional Information\n\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\n- Status version: nightly April 12, 0.12.0\n- Operating System: Android 6.0.1, real Galaxy S6",
